The Journal of Free Software and Free Knowledge is about the approaches demonstrated first by the Free Software movement in creation, collation, redistribution, dissemination and ownership of knowledge, as applied to different intellectual, technological and physical artefacts such as computer software & hardware, music, literature, science, the arts, culture, philosophy or religion, and leading to free and open knowledge



